 TRENTON, Mich. (AP) â€” Authorities say an 18-year-old man who attacked officers with a lawnmower blade has died after being shot by police.

The shooting happened around 4:30 p.m. Thursday at a home in Trenton.

Police say they responded to reports of a young man who was highly agitated and, after officers arrived at the home, the man attacked them with the blade.

Police say they first tried to subdue the man with a stun gun before the shooting. State police say he was taken to a hospital, where he died Friday morning. His name wasn't immediately released.

An injured officer had a cut hand and was treated before being released from the hospital. The attack and shooting are under investigation by state police.